[{"id":"VR814818","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a horizontal axis. The values 0 through 6 r, in increments of r, are indicated. A particle with charge positive Q is indicated at 0, and a particle with charge positive 4 Q is indicated at 6 r.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR814818.g01.svg\"/></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Two charged particles with charges of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"Positive Q\"><math alttext=\"Positive Q\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mpadded><mo>+</mo><mi>Q</mi></mpadded></math></span></span> and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"Positive 4 Q\"><math alttext=\"Positive 4 Q\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mpadded><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>Q</mi></mpadded></math></span></span> on a line are a distance <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"6 r\"><math alttext=\"6 r\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>6</mn><mi>r</mi></math></span></span> apart from each other, as shown in the figure. An observer records the magnitude of the electric field first at a distance <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"r\"><math alttext=\"r\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>r</mi></math></span></span> away from the left particle, and continues to record the magnitude of the electric field consecutively at <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2 r\"><math alttext=\"2 r\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn><mi>r</mi></math></span></span>, <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"3 r\"><math alttext=\"3 r\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>3</mn><mi>r</mi></math></span></span>, <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"4 r\"><math alttext=\"4 r\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>4</mn><mi>r</mi></math></span></span> and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"5 r\"><math alttext=\"5 r\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>5</mn><mi>r</mi></math></span></span>. Which of the following correctly describes the observed magnitudes of electric field during the recordings?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR814818_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The magnitude of the electric field steadily increases.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The magnitude of the electric field remains constant.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The magnitude of the electric field first increases, then decreases.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The magnitude of the electric field first decreases, then increases</p>"],"answer":3}]